divs: Sighting Detailsthis happened when I was @ 16 years old, i'm 32 now. I was watching bats in my front yard when I heard a low hum. I looked west and saw a cube shaped object with 5 or 6 dim brownish bars of light that ran horizontaly along it. I remember estimating it's size to be about the same as an average house. It was flying about 150 to 200 yards above the ground, around 30 mpr. at the time (i was 16) I thought I was watching a satelite landing at the air force academy. At the time I didn't think twice about it being extraterrestrial. I always had thought how lucky I was to see something so cool, untill I got older and realized that satelites don't land.
